h 31  1940  Given to a member of the fourth class who has exhibited outstanding scholarship  conduct and character  the recipient receives a  100 credit towards tuition or fees  The William Brent Bell  67 This award was established in 1970 as a memorial to First Lieutenant Bell who was killed when his helicopter was shot down by enemy fire in Vietnam in March 1969  It was established by his parents  relatives  classmates and friends to recognize a Third Class Cadet who has shown excellence in military studies as did Lieutenant Bell while at VMI  The recipient receives a cash prize of  100 and an engraved saber  The VMI Distinguished Third Class Leadership Award This award was established  by Nathaniel W  Pendleton  Junior  VMI Class of 1957  to encourage and recognize praiseworthy leadership in the proper practical education  training and development of fourth class cadets by a member of the Third Class  It is given to a third class cadet who has participated as a member of the new cadet training cadre who has exhibited the most praiseworthy leadership  The award recipient will receive a cash prize of  250 and a collection of books on leadership  The Association of Military Colleges and Schools of the United States This award is given to a graduating cadet who has demonstrated significant improvement in leadership skills  The award is a medal supplied by AMSCUS  The Purple Heart Scholarship The Purple Heart Scholarship from The Association Of Military Colleges and Schools of the United States in recognition of outstanding leadership  exceptional service and distinctive performance in all areas of cadet life  and for valuable and unselfish support of Virginia Military Institute  The award is a check and a certificate  The Col  Thomas H  Trumps   79 Commandant of Cadets Award This award was established in 2014 by the Class of 1979  It is given to a graduating first class private who has accepted an active duty commission in one of the Armed Forces  and has demonstrated active participation in and served in a leadership role in one of the VMI club sports  The recipient receives a check and a certificate  The Veteran s Recognition Award This award was established in 2012 by the Commandant of Cadets  Colonel Thomas H  Trumps  VMI Class of 1979  to recognize a cadet who is a veteran of active duty military service and has continued to serve through exemplary leadership and mentorship in the corps of cadets  The recipient will receive an engraved mug and a check  The Community Service This award was established in 2012 by the Commandant of Cadets  Colonel Thomas H  Trumps  VMI Class of 1979  to recognize a cadet who served as an emergency medical technician  firefighter or rescue squad member  The recipient will receive a personally embroidered medical travel kit and  100  The Fit Cadet Award This award was established in 2012 by the Commandant of Cadets  Colonel Thomas H  Trumps  VMI Class of 1979  to recognize the male and female cadets achieving the highest VFT score during the academic year  The recipients will receive an engraved sports bottle and a check  The 3rd Class Marksmanship Award This award was established in 2012 by Colonel Thomas H  Trumps   79 to recognize the company with the highest scoring average with the M 16 AR 15 service rifle  The award is given to the company with the highest average score on the 25 meter alternate course  c  qualification target  Company scores also count towards the overall Commandant s Cup award  The North Post Challenge Award This award was established in 2012 by Colonel Thomas H  Trumps   79 to recognize the company team with the highest combined fitness and marksmanship score  The award is given to the company team with the highest score in the following events  swimming  foot march  trap shoot  rifle marksmanship  rock climbing  obstacle course  and confidence climb  Company score will also count towards the overall commandant s cup award  The first  second and third place company teams will also receive individual hand crafted sheath knives  The Company Cup for Academic Achievement This award was proposed in October 1969 by cadets Carson L  Tucker  First Battalion Commander and William P  Williams  First Battalion Adjutant who wrote   for it is possible to utilize the company system here at VMI to influence the academic endeavors of at least fourth classmen  who are particularly impressionable during their first year at the Institute  By bringing academic achievement onto a par with military and physical training achievement  the importance of academic excellence  or  at least  academic stability  will be manifested to impressionable young cadets  The Dean of the Faculty  Colonel James M  Morgan  agreed and the Company Cup was awarded for the first time on May 12  1970  to Company D  commanded by Cadet Captain Robert F  E  Quinlan  The company with the highest combined average GPA for the fall and spring semesters is awarded the company cup upon which their company and year is engraved and a distinctive red streamer is displayed on their guide on upon award and during the following academic year  Commandant s Cup On January 30th  1959  The Commandant Of Cadets  Colonel Glover S  Johns Junior  wrote a letter to General William H  Milton Junior  VMI s Eighth Superintendent  proposing the establishment the Commandant s Cup awarded  to the cadet company making the best score in certain aspects of physical training  His proposal was approved  Colonel Johns designed the sterling silver trophy  approximately 18 inches in height  bearing the distinctive VMI monogram  to be given to the company excelling each year in physical fitness  His objective was improving the physical condition of the corps as a whole  The cup is engraved as follows  Virginia Military Institute Commandant s Cup presented annually to the company most outstanding in physical training and fair specimens of citizen soldiers  The awarding of this cup was discontinued in 1970 except for 1979 and 1985  The company with the highest average score on the VFT for the academic year was awarded the cup  In 2012 the Third Class Marksmanship competition and North Post Challenge  results were added to the computation along with the company VFT pass rate  Garnett Andrews Cup Mr  Garnett Andrews  VMI Class of 1890  donated the Garnett Andrews Cup in 1915 which was presented to the company scoring highest in military efficiency throughout the year  Scoring for the Garnett Andrews Cup competition is based on the company s general efficiency as a military unit which includes the company s performance in drill  ceremonies  parade appearance  meal march downs and guard mounts  Superientendent s Cup This cup is awarded to the company with the highest cumulative point total in the three scored areas of academics  military efficiency and physical fitness  The superintendent s cup is also an incentive for companies to  keep trying  during the year since the award is based on the highest cumulative point total across the three areas not the highest point total of the individual cups  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 